definition[0]: if something is left, it remains after everything else has gone, been taken away, or used
example[0]: I’ve only got a few dollars left.
example[1]: There were a couple of seats left at the back.
example[2]: We don’t have much time left.
example[3]: He pointed to what was left of the house  (=used when very little is left).
example[4]: All that was left was a pile of bones.
example[5]: After we’ve paid the bills, there’s never much left over.
example[6]: They ate some bread rolls left over from the night before.
